<author><name><![CDATA[3gengames]]></name></author>
<updated>2014-10-05T15:12:28-07:00</updated>
<published>2014-10-05T15:12:28-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11897&amp;p=134639#p134639</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11897&amp;p=134639#p134639"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Why is the SNES on screen color pallete so small?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11897&amp;p=134639#p134639"><![CDATA[
8 bit data buses, as 8 bits gives you 256 colors to choose from. Going bigger would mean you'd have to have that much more RAM for displaying them, that much more RAM for storing them, and more speed to process them in some cases. 256 isn't a little though, NES only has up to 19 on screen at once normally.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Sun Oct 05, 2014 3:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
